127
00:08:18,840 --> 00:08:21,760
It has been a year after you came to Shunyuan,

128
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:26,440
but there is no progress on your task.

129
00:08:27,280 --> 00:08:29,610
The leadership is already disappointed.

130
00:08:30,320 --> 00:08:31,680
It's not good

131
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:33,730
for you to keep delaying it.

132
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:34,760
Yes.

133
00:08:35,549 --> 00:08:36,669
I got it.

134
00:08:37,030 --> 00:08:38,669
Still no specific location?

135
00:08:39,669 --> 00:08:41,120
The Russian has died,

136
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:42,549
and the map is a fake one.

137
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:44,400
That translator

138
00:08:44,540 --> 00:08:46,640
can only draw a general location.

139
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:49,160
Maybe he really doesn't know anything.

140
00:08:49,440 --> 00:08:51,520
No one can survive that kind of torture.

141
00:08:51,520 --> 00:08:53,000
This is classified now.

142
00:08:53,540 --> 00:08:56,440
I heard that the translator has escaped.

143
00:08:57,320 --> 00:08:59,520
You should bring him back as soon as possible.

144
00:08:59,520 --> 00:09:00,320
Yes.

145
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:02,330
I've already sent someone to do it.

146
00:09:02,520 --> 00:09:03,640
And the real map,

147
00:09:03,920 --> 00:09:05,520
should be found soon too.

148
00:09:05,920 --> 00:09:06,640
Yes.

149
00:09:09,040 --> 00:09:10,560
They are the geologists

150
00:09:10,760 --> 00:09:13,320
sent by Mr. Yamamoto.

151
00:09:13,960 --> 00:09:17,080
They will cooperate with you next.

152
00:09:25,660 --> 00:09:26,960
Please don't worry.

153
00:09:27,920 --> 00:09:30,050
I will find the map as soon as possible.

154
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:33,920
Mr. Li,

155
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:36,640
is that one just now your friend?

156
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:38,860
My neighbor next door.

157
00:09:39,920 --> 00:09:40,760
Where is he?

158
00:09:41,880 --> 00:09:42,800
Went back home.

159
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:45,640
But, his flowers…

160
00:09:45,640 --> 00:09:46,900
I can bring them to him.

161
00:09:47,240 --> 00:09:48,760
- Alright, thank you. - Give them to me.

162
00:09:48,760 --> 00:09:49,440
Wait.

163
00:09:49,800 --> 00:09:50,860
Your hand got hurt?

164
00:09:51,840 --> 00:09:52,900
It's not a big deal.

165
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:53,880
I'm fine.

166
00:09:54,280 --> 00:09:54,660
Wait a second.

167
00:09:54,660 --> 00:09:55,990
Let me bind it up for you.

168
00:10:15,840 --> 00:10:16,560
You...

169
00:10:17,640 --> 00:10:19,040
You can bind up injuries?

170
00:10:19,040 --> 00:10:19,920
Not so well.

171
00:10:21,760 --> 00:10:24,090
But it may be like wrapping up the flowers.

172
00:11:22,120 --> 00:11:22,720
Alright.

173
00:11:24,880 --> 00:11:25,800
That's it?

174
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:28,760
This is so ugly.

175
00:11:29,080 --> 00:11:29,940
Don't touch it!

176
00:11:30,320 --> 00:11:31,680
I think it's pretty.

177
00:11:32,040 --> 00:11:32,960
Trust me.

178
00:11:32,960 --> 00:11:34,480
I never tell lies.

179
00:11:41,660 --> 00:11:43,190
Let me bring you some water.

180
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:44,130
I'm not thirsty.

181
00:11:46,920 --> 00:11:47,840
Well,

182
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:49,930
are you busy in a moment?

183
00:11:51,240 --> 00:11:52,000
No.

184
00:11:52,660 --> 00:11:53,320
Well,

185
00:11:53,540 --> 00:11:54,740
don't you want water?

186
00:11:55,840 --> 00:11:56,560
No.

187
00:11:57,360 --> 00:11:58,400
And any food?

188
00:11:58,660 --> 00:11:59,400
No.

189
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:01,930
Then, could you help me with some work?

190
00:12:02,640 --> 00:12:03,000
What?

191
00:12:03,640 --> 00:12:04,640
Are we familiar?

192
00:12:05,280 --> 00:12:06,160
Sure.

193
00:12:06,360 --> 00:12:07,690
I can even remember you.

194
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:10,720
You are Mr. Li Wenzhong from Baihua Company.

195
00:12:12,760 --> 00:12:14,000
Just help me move something.

196
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:15,160
It's easy. Wait.

197
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:18,040
But, I got hurt!

198
00:13:50,400 --> 00:13:52,160
I have done what I should do.

199
00:13:52,280 --> 00:13:53,320
What else?

200
00:13:53,520 --> 00:13:54,280
No.

201
00:13:54,280 --> 00:13:55,340
Thank you for this.

202
00:13:56,600 --> 00:13:57,460
Nothing at all.

203
00:13:57,640 --> 00:13:58,280
But,

204
00:13:58,400 --> 00:13:59,320
do you have

205
00:13:59,660 --> 00:14:01,280
such a heavy workload every day?

206
00:14:01,280 --> 00:14:02,080
No.

207
00:14:02,080 --> 00:14:02,880
These are for a month.

208
00:14:02,880 --> 00:14:03,520
What?

209
00:14:05,440 --> 00:14:06,240
Mr. Li,

210
00:14:06,240 --> 00:14:07,840
you are indeed a soldier.

211
00:14:07,840 --> 00:14:09,520
So tall and so strong.

212
00:14:09,520 --> 00:14:10,280
You can even

213
00:14:10,280 --> 00:14:12,340
finish the work for a month in one day!

214
00:14:14,440 --> 00:14:15,280
Thank you!

215
00:14:15,660 --> 00:14:17,190
It should be me who say this.

216
00:14:17,400 --> 00:14:18,760
Let me treat you the dinner.

217
00:14:18,760 --> 00:14:20,120
You treat me?

218
00:14:20,360 --> 00:14:21,480
Do you have money?

219
00:14:23,760 --> 00:14:24,600
Sure.

220
00:14:24,600 --> 00:14:25,280
Look.

221
00:14:28,800 --> 00:14:29,400
Fine.

222
00:14:30,360 --> 00:14:32,090
Let me change my clothes first.

223
00:14:41,640 --> 00:14:42,480
Is that heavy?

224
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:44,160
No. I'm used to it.

225
00:14:44,320 --> 00:14:45,650
I always forget things.

226
00:14:46,080 --> 00:14:47,320
This can help me.

227
00:14:47,320 --> 00:14:47,960
Let's go.

228
00:14:48,520 --> 00:14:49,450
Let me treat you.

229
00:14:51,480 --> 00:14:52,240
Walk this side.

230
00:14:52,240 --> 00:14:53,370
Or you'll fall down.

231
00:14:55,840 --> 00:14:58,240
How about I treat you…

232
00:14:58,400 --> 00:14:59,200
noodles?

233
00:14:59,880 --> 00:15:00,400
No.

234
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:03,520
What about dumplings?

235
00:15:04,720 --> 00:15:05,800
I want western food.

236
00:15:05,800 --> 00:15:07,240
But that'll be expensive.

237
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:07,920
Yeah.

238
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:08,960
Your treat.

239
00:15:09,120 --> 00:15:09,720
Yes.

240
00:15:09,880 --> 00:15:11,680
But I can't afford western food.

241
00:15:12,120 --> 00:15:12,920
Then I treat you.

242
00:15:12,920 --> 00:15:13,520
No, no.

243
00:15:13,520 --> 00:15:14,640
We had a deal.

244
00:15:15,680 --> 00:15:16,740
I should treat you.

245
00:15:17,320 --> 00:15:18,380
Noodles, alright?

246
00:15:31,720 --> 00:15:33,120
You know what, if you bully her again,

247
00:15:33,120 --> 00:15:34,180
I'll beat you up...

248
00:15:47,200 --> 00:15:47,800
Wenzhong!

249
00:15:48,360 --> 00:15:49,120
Let's go have dinner.

250
00:15:49,120 --> 00:15:50,120
I have had.

251
00:15:50,120 --> 00:15:50,880
What?

252
00:15:52,640 --> 00:15:53,900
Well, I'm leaving now.

253
00:16:30,880 --> 00:16:32,040
My mom made ginseng soup.

254
00:16:32,040 --> 00:16:33,170
Get up and have some.

255
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:36,640
Why soup again?

256
00:16:36,760 --> 00:16:38,160
I'm so tired of that.

257
00:16:38,400 --> 00:16:39,760
She said you are in poor health now

258
00:16:39,760 --> 00:16:40,890
and you need energy.

259
00:16:41,280 --> 00:16:42,240
Have it now.

260
00:16:53,040 --> 00:16:53,840
Take it easy.

261
00:16:53,840 --> 00:16:54,840
Look what you did.

262
00:17:02,880 --> 00:17:04,210
What are you looking at?

263
00:17:06,880 --> 00:17:07,400
What?

264
00:17:08,069 --> 00:17:09,270
There is the soup too!

265
00:17:09,760 --> 00:17:10,880
Enough.

266
00:17:12,829 --> 00:17:14,240
I'm a patient, OK?

267
00:17:15,480 --> 00:17:16,410
I don't think so.

268
00:17:16,720 --> 00:17:17,720
You're so energetic.

269
00:17:17,720 --> 00:17:18,980
Even stronger than me.

270
00:17:20,440 --> 00:17:21,349
What's wrong?

271
00:17:21,880 --> 00:17:23,000
Does it hurt again?

272
00:17:23,960 --> 00:17:24,560
No.

273
00:17:25,829 --> 00:17:26,690
Let me see that.

274
00:17:27,040 --> 00:17:28,170
It's not necessary.

275
00:17:28,280 --> 00:17:29,080
Let me see!

276
00:17:29,080 --> 00:17:30,000
Hands off!

277
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:31,280
My mom will see this!

278
00:17:31,600 --> 00:17:32,760
So what?

279
00:17:35,720 --> 00:17:36,720
You know what,

280
00:17:37,240 --> 00:17:38,880
your mom likes me so much.

281
00:17:39,800 --> 00:17:40,930
She looked at me as if

282
00:17:41,080 --> 00:17:43,000
she was looking at her future son-in-law.

283
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:43,960
Don't flatter yourself.

284
00:17:43,960 --> 00:17:44,960
That's real!

285
00:17:51,600 --> 00:17:53,440
So many things happened these days.

286
00:17:53,440 --> 00:17:55,440
How about you find a temple to worship?

287
00:17:55,440 --> 00:17:57,280
Can you talk seriously?

288
00:17:57,600 --> 00:17:58,720
I'm not kidding.

289
00:17:59,100 --> 00:18:00,480
Do you know who did that?

290
00:18:03,200 --> 00:18:04,480
I heard that

291
00:18:04,680 --> 00:18:05,810
it was the Japanese.

292
00:18:06,040 --> 00:18:06,960
Japanese?

293
00:18:07,600 --> 00:18:08,960
Was it because

294
00:18:09,160 --> 00:18:10,360
they had known I went

295
00:18:10,720 --> 00:18:12,450
to the hospital to save people?

296
00:18:13,340 --> 00:18:14,600
If it were really them,

297
00:18:14,880 --> 00:18:15,960
they could have just killed you,

298
00:18:15,960 --> 00:18:17,220
why did they catch you?

299
00:18:19,340 --> 00:18:20,200
Maybe it was

300
00:18:20,560 --> 00:18:21,690
because of that boy.

301
00:18:23,520 --> 00:18:24,480
There was a boy

302
00:18:24,480 --> 00:18:26,000
